ries of governing are remade and the peoples constituted; how the public domain is re-imagined and new forms of state-citizen relationships fostered and how the remaking of governance shapes our understanding of politics, changing the ways in which citizens engage with political power and the selves they bring to that engagement.  Remaking governance is essential reading for academics and students across a range of social science disciplines, and of interest to those engaged in policy evaluation and reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPolicy sciencesvCongresses. 0aPolitical participationzEuropean Union countriesvCongresses. 0aPublic administrationzEuropean Union countriesvCongresses. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aBang, Henrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarmel, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClarke, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHvinden, Bjørn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohansson, Håkan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLendvai, Noémi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewman, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewman, Janet, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSaward, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSterling, Rebekah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978186134639140uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781847421388?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97818474213